  <body>
    
    <p>
      Welcome to <b>thinkContext</b>, the web browser extension which adds contextually relevant, politically progressive information to your web browsing.  For more information visit our website at <a href="http://thinkcontext.org/" target="_blank">thinkcontext.org</a> or follow us on <a href="https://twitter.com/thinkcontext" target="_blank">Twitter</a>.
    </p>
<div style="float: right; display: inline; width: 500px">
Important for Safari users!  Make sure you set Safari to automatically update extensions.

<img src="icons/safari-autoupdate.png">
</div>
    <p>
      As you browse the web <b>thinkContext</b> consults several progressive data sources and if it finds anything relevant to what you are looking at it will unobtrusively add that information right into the page.  Look for the icons shown next to the data sources below and hover your mouse over them to show more information.
    </p>
    <p>
      Below you may configure <b>thinkContext</b>, including how it behaves and which data sources it consults.  We recommend to begin with that you take the default configureation and only change things if you have a specific reason to do.
    </p>

    <div id="status"></div>
    <button id="save">Save</button>    
    <br>

<h3>Data Sources</h3>
    <table>
      <tr>
	<td>
	  <input type="checkbox" id="opt_news">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <img src="icons/trackback-16.png">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <b>Progressive News Trackback</b> - See what progressive blogs and news sources are saying about the mainstream news you are reading.  <b>thinkContext</b> scans over 50 progressive news sources such as <a href="http://www.thenation.com/" target="_blank">The Nation</a>, <a href="http://www.earthjustice.org/" target="_blank">Earthjustice</a>, <a href="http://colorlines.com/" target="_blank">Colorlines</a>, and <a href="http://www.feministing.com/" target="_blank">Feministing</a>.  For a full list <a href="http://www.thinkcontext.org/" target="_blank">see here</a>.
	</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
	<td>
	  <input type="checkbox" id="opt_hotel">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <img src="icons/greenCheck.png">
	  <img src="icons/redCirc.png">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <b>Union Hotels</b> - Using the <a href="http://www.hotelworkersrising.org/HotelGuide" taget="_blank">Union Hotel Guide</a> put out by <a href="http://www.hotelworkersrising.org/" target="_blank">Hotel Workers Rising</a> this feature will show you which hotels have union workers and which are involved involved in a labor dispute.
	</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
	<td>
	  <input type="checkbox" id="opt_green">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <img src="icons/greenG.png">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <b>Green Business Information</b> - highlights companies listed in <a href="http://www.greenpages.org/" target="_blank">The Green Pages</a>.
	</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
	<td>
	  <input type="checkbox" id="opt_rush">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <img src="icons/sr.png">
	</td>
	<td>
	  <b>Rush Limbaugh</b> advertisers using data from <a href="http://stoprush.net/" target="_blank">stoprush.net</a>
	</td>
      </tr>
      
    </table>

